# A hypothesis is FULLY render-time config: the orchestrator substitutes the five
# placeholders below (NO code edits between hypotheses). The footer then builds
# ONLY CONFIG['axis'] and runs ONLY CONFIG['labeler'] as ONE cell, sizing with
# CONFIG['sizing'] + CONFIG['thresh'] (same rule reused in infer OOS).
#   axis    in bar_builder.AXES (dollar,tick,vol,range,logdollar,entropy)
#   labeler in labeler.LABELERS (kmeans2stage,carry,tertile,bgm,agglomerative,
#                                triple_barrier,multi_horizon,hmm,always_long)
#   thresh  per-ETF entry threshold (e.g. 0.10-0.55)
#   sizing  in {ramp, binary, cdf_plain, cdf_overlay}
# BACK-COMPAT: if __AXIS__/__LABELER__ are left literal (not substituted), the
# footer ignores CONFIG and falls back to the existing full sweep, so the old
# per-axis drivers (render_script(ticker, axis)) keep working unchanged.
def _cfg_or(val, placeholder, fallback):
    return fallback if val == placeholder else val


